1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,962
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:04,045 --> 00:00:07,632
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,552
<i>- ♪ Fix it</i> ♪
<i>- ♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,635 --> 00:00:12,762
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,846 --> 00:00:15,724
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:18,101
[in English] Daddy!

7
00:00:18,601 --> 00:00:20,937
[Cita] Hi, Janine! I'm Miss Cita!

8
00:00:21,020 --> 00:00:22,021
Are you the maid here?

9
00:00:22,105 --> 00:00:23,231
[Tonet] <i>It's fine!</i>

10
00:00:23,314 --> 00:00:26,151
<i>Then I'll just look for another man.</i>

11
00:00:26,234 --> 00:00:27,235
[Janine] Hi, Ibyang!

12
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:29,446
What are you doing here?

13
00:00:29,529 --> 00:00:31,948
She'll stay in your room.
You'll share a room.

14
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:33,742
[Janine] <i>It's like she doesn't</i>
<i>want me here.</i>

15
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:35,326
- [in English] Catch!
- [all squeal and gasp]

16
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:36,244
[Cathy, in English] Oh my God!

17
00:00:36,327 --> 00:00:38,580
- [Karla] Hey, water! Oh, no!
- [Ame] It's burning! Water, water!

18
00:00:38,663 --> 00:00:40,457
- [Karla] Brother Kurt, water!
- [Janine] I'm here

19
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:42,417
because you might take Daddy away from me.

20
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,836
- [Janine] Leave, leave!
- [Ibyang gasps]

21
00:00:44,919 --> 00:00:46,004
- [Janine] Leave!
- [Ibyang] Hey!

22
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:49,424
[Atoy] Did you fight with Janine again,
that's why you can't sleep?

23
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:50,425
Come, lie down beside me, here.

24
00:00:50,508 --> 00:00:52,552
- [Atoy] What?
- It doesn't fit.

25
00:00:52,635 --> 00:00:56,222
[Janine] I'm not used
to sleeping alone here.

26
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:58,767
Huh? Oh, come on.

27
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:01,853
PREVIOUSLY

28
00:01:16,451 --> 00:01:18,620
[music fades]

29
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:28,963
[squeals, in Visayan] Oh my! You kid!

30
00:01:29,047 --> 00:01:30,256
[Tonet gasping]

31
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:31,800
You… You're here.

32
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:33,718
[in English] Good morning!

33
00:01:34,719 --> 00:01:36,304
You're my daddy's maid, right?

34
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:38,890
[sneaky music playing]

35
00:01:38,973 --> 00:01:40,099
It's still so early, huh.

36
00:01:40,850 --> 00:01:42,936
I'll tear this kid apart.

37
00:01:45,522 --> 00:01:46,898
I'm actually an assistant.

38
00:01:46,981 --> 00:01:48,108
[titters]

39
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:49,484
Exactly, you're a maid.

40
00:01:49,567 --> 00:01:51,111
Either a maid or an assistant.

41
00:01:51,194 --> 00:01:52,862
It's the same thing.
What's wrong with you?

42
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:55,532
[stammers]

43
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:57,826
Uh, do you need anything? [titters]

44
00:02:06,918 --> 00:02:09,129
Hey. Oh, you're naughty!

45
00:02:09,212 --> 00:02:10,839
That belongs to your father!

46
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:12,549
He might get mad.

47
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:17,720
[music fades]

48
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:18,930
[Janine] Well, it's my daddy's anyway.

49
00:02:19,013 --> 00:02:20,265
[music ends]

50
00:02:20,348 --> 00:02:21,724
Why are you stopping me?

51
00:02:22,225 --> 00:02:23,351
[titters]

52
00:02:23,434 --> 00:02:27,313
Because if it goes missing,
your daddy will suffer, okay?

53
00:02:27,397 --> 00:02:30,191
Yes, he'll have a hard time.
He'll suffer, right?

54
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:31,109
‪[quirky sting]

55
00:02:33,444 --> 00:02:35,488
[sneaky music playing]

56
00:02:36,906 --> 00:02:37,991
Hmm.

57
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:40,368
What kind of child is that?

58
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:43,746
She's so small yet already growing horns.

59
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:45,582
[sighs]

60
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:49,085
[softly] Oh, my.

61
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:51,004
So many papers.

62
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,346
[rousing music playing]

63
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:01,806
AB positive?

64
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:03,308
[suspicious music playing]

65
00:03:03,391 --> 00:03:04,517
Hmm.

66
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:07,061
That child has blue blood.

67
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:10,982
No wonder she acts like…
a snooty princess.

68
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:14,402
[suave theme music playing]

69
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:41,012
[music fades]

70
00:03:51,814 --> 00:03:54,400
[light music playing]

71
00:04:07,330 --> 00:04:09,457
[in English] Oh? Good morning.

72
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:16,756
Ibyang. What are you doing?

73
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:17,840
[music fades]

74
00:04:18,508 --> 00:04:22,804
Uh, making Tatoy's coffee.

75
00:04:23,304 --> 00:04:25,890
Because Tatoy likes the way I mix it.

76
00:04:25,974 --> 00:04:28,768
[light music playing]

77
00:04:32,897 --> 00:04:35,024
- Tatoy, your coffee.
- Ibyang.

78
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:37,527
Hey!

79
00:04:38,194 --> 00:04:39,195
[in English] Wow!

80
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,280
[mug clinks]

81
00:04:40,363 --> 00:04:41,739
It smells so good.

82
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:43,908
[chuckles, inhales]

83
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:44,993
Hmm.

84
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:47,704
[slurps]

85
00:04:47,787 --> 00:04:49,664
[exhales] Strong.

86
00:04:49,747 --> 00:04:53,668
Oh, Ibyang really makes good coffee.

87
00:04:53,751 --> 00:04:55,670
- [chuckles softly] Right?
- [chuckles softly]

88
00:04:55,753 --> 00:04:59,090
Um… Daddy, I also know how to make coffee.

89
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:02,927
It's better than Ibyang's blend.

90
00:05:03,011 --> 00:05:04,220
Really?

91
00:05:05,263 --> 00:05:06,514
[sneaky music playing]

92
00:05:06,597 --> 00:05:12,103
Uh… Maybe both your coffees
taste delicious, right?

93
00:05:12,186 --> 00:05:13,896
Maybe. What do you think?

94
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:15,273
[Janine] Ah, wait.

95
00:05:15,356 --> 00:05:17,150
I'll make one. I'll let you try.

96
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:18,192
[Atoy] Okay, okay, okay.

97
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:25,658
[exhales]

98
00:05:30,413 --> 00:05:32,540
Um, where's the sugar?

99
00:05:34,792 --> 00:05:35,752
Why don't you leave?

100
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:36,753
- [Janine] Leave!
- [Ibyang gasps]

101
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:43,009
Um, Ibyang, show her where the jars are.

102
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:47,555
Where's the sugar?

103
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:48,848
Hurry!

104
00:05:56,773 --> 00:05:57,899
Here.

105
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:00,443
[music fades]

106
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:05,364
[sneaky music playing]

107
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:06,324
[Janine] What?

108
00:06:17,668 --> 00:06:18,878
Put this back.

109
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:27,136
[music fades]

110
00:06:29,597 --> 00:06:33,059
[playful music playing]

111
00:06:43,027 --> 00:06:44,278
[utensils clatter]

112
00:06:47,949 --> 00:06:49,534
- [music fades]
- [Janine] Here, Daddy.

113
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:50,660
[Atoy] Hmm?

114
00:06:50,743 --> 00:06:53,496
[sneaky music playing]

115
00:06:53,579 --> 00:06:55,540
Wow, impressive.

116
00:06:55,623 --> 00:06:56,666
Wow.

117
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:58,918
Mm-hmm.

118
00:06:59,001 --> 00:07:00,002
[chuckles softly]

119
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:03,172
- [mug clinks]
- Wow.

120
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:04,966
Perfect, coffee in the morning.

121
00:07:08,052 --> 00:07:09,637
[exhales]

122
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:12,098
[chuckles]

123
00:07:12,181 --> 00:07:13,307
Nice.

124
00:07:18,896 --> 00:07:19,814
[music fades]

125
00:07:19,897 --> 00:07:20,773
Hmm?

126
00:07:21,816 --> 00:07:23,609
[retches, spits]

127
00:07:23,693 --> 00:07:26,446
[playful music playing]

128
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:29,740
Ah! It tastes salty.

129
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:37,248
[Janine] Um…

130
00:07:37,790 --> 00:07:41,669
No, it's not salty.
Promise. I put sugar in it.

131
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:43,713
- Sugar?
- [Janine] S-Sugar.

132
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:47,884
[music fades]

133
00:07:49,677 --> 00:07:50,511
[huffs]

134
00:07:50,595 --> 00:07:53,139
[playful music playing]

135
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:10,907
Was that the right thing to do?

136
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:18,289
But she was the one
who gave you the salty coffee.

137
00:08:18,915 --> 00:08:20,875
- [Atoy] Oh?
- Why are you angry with me?

138
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:23,127
Yes, of course.

139
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:29,050
Because you deliberately
gave her the container of salt.

140
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:31,969
You knew it was salt, didn't you?

141
00:08:32,053 --> 00:08:34,305
Look what happened. The coffee was wasted.

142
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:38,476
It was just a prank.

143
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,560
[Atoy] What?

144
00:08:40,269 --> 00:08:42,522
What did you say? It's a…?

145
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:43,731
- Prank.
- A prank?!

146
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,108
[pensive music playing]

147
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:47,443
Oh, you…

148
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,028
Is that what they teach
in your school now?

149
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:50,738
Those pranks?

150
00:08:52,949 --> 00:08:54,408
[in English] Sorry.

151
00:08:55,243 --> 00:08:59,497
Ibyang, I want you and Janine
to make peace, okay?

152
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:00,498
[Ibyang sniffles]

153
00:09:00,581 --> 00:09:02,208
I don't want this to happen again.

154
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:03,543
Huh?

155
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:05,670
I don't want you two fighting.
You must fix this.

156
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:07,713
[Atoy] Do you understand?

157
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:10,383
I want you to apologize to her.

158
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,094
What?

159
00:09:14,053 --> 00:09:15,263
You will apologize.

160
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:17,598
You did something wrong.

161
00:09:18,432 --> 00:09:19,892
So, you must do what is right.

162
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:27,191
Ibyang, you must do what is right
even when no one is watching.

163
00:09:27,275 --> 00:09:28,901
Even when no one sees.

164
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:30,820
Okay?

165
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:33,906
You will correct this. Fix it.

166
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:37,368
Yes.

167
00:09:38,744 --> 00:09:40,538
I want you to be on good terms
when I return, all right?

168
00:09:40,621 --> 00:09:42,498
No more fighting.

169
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:44,542
- [Atoy] Okay?
- Yes.

170
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:46,836
[Atoy] All right.

171
00:09:59,181 --> 00:10:01,684
[light music playing]

172
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:06,731
"BE A HERO
DONATE BLOOD TODAY"

173
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:25,499
[woman] Thank you again. Sit down first.

174
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:26,834
- Thank you.
- You might get dizzy.

175
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:28,210
It's fine. That's okay.

176
00:10:28,836 --> 00:10:30,713
[Siony] Oh, here. Drink some juice first.

177
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:32,465
- Are you okay?
- Yes, yes.

178
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:33,633
We're used to this.

179
00:10:33,716 --> 00:10:35,468
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

180
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:36,719
Are there many in line?

181
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:38,929
Yes. Thank you for donating.

182
00:10:39,013 --> 00:10:40,139
Of course.

183
00:10:40,222 --> 00:10:42,224
Again and again. Oh, that's it… That's it.

184
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:43,893
[Atoy] Oh, Mister Nestor!

185
00:10:43,976 --> 00:10:45,144
- Atoy.
- [Atoy] You're here…

186
00:10:45,227 --> 00:10:46,687
Perfect. You're next.

187
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:48,481
- Will you donate?
- Ah-- Oh, no.

188
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:51,233
Maybe tomorrow. I don't feel well.

189
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:52,276
- [Atoy] Oh?
- Ah, I feel--

190
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:53,402
I have a slight fever.

191
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:55,279
If you have a slight fever,
you're not allowed to donate?

192
00:10:56,238 --> 00:10:58,407
- [chuckles] Hmm?
- You're just making excuses!

193
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:01,285
- No, look, I really have one
- [Atoy] You're just making excuses…

194
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:03,871
- [Siony] Oh. You don't have a fever!
- I do.

195
00:11:03,954 --> 00:11:06,707
- No!
- You're next. Come on…

196
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:08,334
[Siony] You just need to write your name.

197
00:11:08,417 --> 00:11:10,628
There's still testing to see
if you can donate.

198
00:11:10,711 --> 00:11:12,380
[light music playing]

199
00:11:12,463 --> 00:11:13,839
- Tonet. Oh?
- [Tonet gasps]

200
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:15,758
Ah! Oh-- What's that?

201
00:11:16,801 --> 00:11:19,303
Ah! Wow!

202
00:11:19,387 --> 00:11:20,721
You already donated.

203
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:21,931
Ah, yes.

204
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:24,266
Maybe it can help somehow.

205
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,935
You? You can donate too.

206
00:11:26,018 --> 00:11:28,354
You definitely can. What's your type?

207
00:11:29,230 --> 00:11:30,064
You.

208
00:11:30,898 --> 00:11:31,982
- [quirky music playing]
- [titters]

209
00:11:32,066 --> 00:11:33,609
Just joking! That's just a joke.

210
00:11:33,692 --> 00:11:35,444
No, I meant…

211
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:36,987
[in English] O positive.

212
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:38,948
- So, you're O positive.
- O positive!

213
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:40,991
You're the same as Atoy!

214
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:43,244
The same. That's good.

215
00:11:43,327 --> 00:11:44,203
You can donate now.

216
00:11:44,286 --> 00:11:47,164
See, we're the same, Atoy.

217
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:50,543
- [in English] I think… it's a sign.
- [chuckles softly]

218
00:11:50,626 --> 00:11:52,545
There are many O positive.

219
00:11:52,628 --> 00:11:55,256
It seems most people are O posi--
Oh, go ahead. You can donate.

220
00:11:55,339 --> 00:11:57,425
Afterwards, don't forget
to return to the shop.

221
00:11:57,508 --> 00:11:58,467
- Yes.
- [in English] Good luck!

222
00:11:58,551 --> 00:11:59,552
Okay, boss!

223
00:11:59,635 --> 00:12:00,511
[Atoy] You can do it.

224
00:12:00,594 --> 00:12:03,055
[sneaky music playing]

225
00:12:16,777 --> 00:12:18,612
[Ibyang] So, you're here!

226
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:20,364
Why?

227
00:12:20,448 --> 00:12:22,158
Will you prank me again?

228
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:24,201
No.

229
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:25,995
I'll apologize to you.

230
00:12:26,745 --> 00:12:29,123
Promise, I won't repeat it.

231
00:12:33,794 --> 00:12:34,920
[Ibyang] Hey!

232
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:36,630
Let's make peace.

233
00:12:37,339 --> 00:12:39,425
So Tatoy will be happy too.

234
00:12:41,218 --> 00:12:42,052
What's this?

235
00:12:42,136 --> 00:12:44,221
- [Janine] I want to try this on.
- [clicks]

236
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:45,389
Hey!

237
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:46,974
Don't pull that!

238
00:12:47,057 --> 00:12:49,226
[suspicious music playing]

239
00:12:53,189 --> 00:12:54,982
[blipping]

240
00:12:55,774 --> 00:12:57,943
Hey, don't go in there!

241
00:12:58,027 --> 00:12:59,153
It's forbidden!

242
00:13:02,781 --> 00:13:03,657
Hey!

243
00:13:03,741 --> 00:13:05,868
You're not supposed to go in there.

244
00:13:06,368 --> 00:13:07,745
Tatoy will get mad!

245
00:13:07,828 --> 00:13:09,455
He won't know.

246
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:14,502
Unless… you tell him.

247
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:17,671
[tense music playing]

248
00:13:17,755 --> 00:13:18,672
[sighs]

249
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:21,675
[device blips]

250
00:13:24,094 --> 00:13:26,555
[inaudible]

251
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:32,770
[Janine] Wow!

252
00:13:33,395 --> 00:13:35,439
[suspicious music playing]

253
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:38,901
Why does Daddy have this?

254
00:13:40,444 --> 00:13:41,946
[Ibyang gasps]

255
00:13:42,029 --> 00:13:44,031
Janine, let's get out.

256
00:13:44,114 --> 00:13:46,659
We'll both get scolded.

257
00:13:47,243 --> 00:13:48,035
[Janine] Wow!

258
00:13:49,036 --> 00:13:50,162
This is so cool.

259
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:51,914
[Janine] So cool!

260
00:13:51,997 --> 00:13:53,290
You're really annoying!

261
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:54,291
Such a troublemaker!

262
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,001
I'm the troublemaker, huh?

263
00:13:57,044 --> 00:13:59,213
- Put that back.
- You're the troublemaker.

264
00:13:59,296 --> 00:14:00,089
What?!

265
00:14:00,172 --> 00:14:03,634
[Ibyang grunting]

266
00:14:03,717 --> 00:14:06,512
[tense music playing]

267
00:14:09,765 --> 00:14:12,893
[rousing music playing]

268
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:16,564
- Tonet!
- Ah!

269
00:14:16,647 --> 00:14:18,691
- Ah, Sis Siony.
- Will you donate now?

270
00:14:18,774 --> 00:14:19,775
Uh, me?

271
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:21,652
Uh, I still have work.

272
00:14:21,735 --> 00:14:22,903
Wait.

273
00:14:22,987 --> 00:14:23,988
Don't leave yet.

274
00:14:24,613 --> 00:14:28,325
Is it true that Atoy has a child
with a rich woman?

275
00:14:28,909 --> 00:14:32,872
That's what I hear from the vermins
here in Tabang Lupa.

276
00:14:32,955 --> 00:14:34,665
It's just that Cita
doesn't really share stories.

277
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:36,083
Is it true?

278
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:38,127
[sneaky music playing]

279
00:14:43,048 --> 00:14:44,758
[inaudible]

280
00:14:44,842 --> 00:14:47,094
Uh, you didn't hear it from me, okay.

281
00:14:47,177 --> 00:14:49,763
But, yes.

282
00:14:51,557 --> 00:14:52,725
[nervous gass]

283
00:14:52,808 --> 00:14:54,310
But the child is unusual…

284
00:14:54,393 --> 00:14:57,938
You wouldn't really expect--

285
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:00,399
Atoy is kind.

286
00:15:00,482 --> 00:15:02,860
So kind, and the mother is okay too.

287
00:15:02,943 --> 00:15:05,821
- [Siony] Hmm…
- But the child, oh my.

288
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:06,864
[clicks tongue]

289
00:15:06,947 --> 00:15:12,870
Like… Like a demon
that turned into a child.

290
00:15:12,953 --> 00:15:15,497
You wouldn't think it's theirs.

291
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:17,082
Maybe not.

292
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:19,919
Maybe she was just picked up somewhere

293
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:22,087
or baby-switched at the hospital.

294
00:15:22,171 --> 00:15:23,839
Like a soap opera.

295
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:26,008
[music fades]

296
00:15:27,217 --> 00:15:28,594
I almost got caught there.

297
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:29,511
[gasps]

298
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:31,472
You're too stubborn.

299
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:33,432
I was just looking.

300
00:15:33,515 --> 00:15:34,642
[tense music playing]

301
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:36,810
Weren't you taught to obey?

302
00:15:37,811 --> 00:15:40,272
Aren't you afraid of being scolded?!

303
00:15:40,981 --> 00:15:41,815
[Ibyang clicks tongue]

304
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:44,234
Learn to obey.

305
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:46,820
Even my mommy can't control me.

306
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:48,197
So how could you?

307
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:50,032
[music fades]

308
00:15:50,115 --> 00:15:51,158
[Paldo] There!

309
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:52,701
[nurse] Thank you. You're so brave.

310
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:53,786
[Paldo] Of course.

311
00:15:54,411 --> 00:15:55,496
- [Paldo] Thanks, nurse.
- [nurse] Thank you.

312
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:59,249
See? Easy!

313
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:01,418
Who's next? Who's next?

314
00:16:01,502 --> 00:16:02,544
- Go.
- This one.

315
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:04,046
- [man] I think it's you!
- [Paldo] You're next.

316
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:05,130
[T-Bak groans]

317
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:06,423
[men Hey! Hey, hey, hey, hey!

318
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:07,549
[T-Bak] You're crazy!

319
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:08,509
Psst. What's that?

320
00:16:08,592 --> 00:16:10,219
It's easy. You can do it!

321
00:16:10,302 --> 00:16:12,638
Wait! I'll just prepare myself!

322
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:14,556
Hey, T-Bak, don't be noisy.

323
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,558
[sneaky music playing]

324
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:18,018
- Should I lie down?
- [nurse] Yes, lie down.

325
00:16:18,102 --> 00:16:19,186
- [T-Bak groans]
- [nurse] Slowly.

326
00:16:19,895 --> 00:16:20,771
[music fades]

327
00:16:20,854 --> 00:16:22,731
[T-Bak] Sis, does it hurt?

328
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:23,691
[nurse] Yes.

329
00:16:24,191 --> 00:16:27,111
[T-Bak] Ouch!

330
00:16:27,194 --> 00:16:28,362
[screams] Ouch!

331
00:16:28,445 --> 00:16:29,863
- [T-Bak cries]
- Hey! Hey, T-Bak!

332
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:31,991
- [T-Bak cries]
- Like you're being circumcised.

333
00:16:32,074 --> 00:16:33,242
- [T-Bak whimpers]
- [Paldo] What's wrong with you?!

334
00:16:33,325 --> 00:16:34,827
It hasn't even started,
and you're screaming.

335
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:35,786
Do you want to just go home?

336
00:16:35,869 --> 00:16:36,787
Just come back tomorrow.

337
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:38,205
Oh, that's right.

338
00:16:38,288 --> 00:16:40,499
Look at Putoy, oh! See?

339
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:43,002
[in English] He's so brave! Oh.

340
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:44,044
[Paldo] He's doing better than you.

341
00:16:44,128 --> 00:16:46,755
Guys, wait a minute. I'll go to the CR.

342
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:47,756
[man] What CR? What does he mean by CR?

343
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,133
[Paldo] Nurse, your needle looks bigger.

344
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:50,592
- [T-Bak gasps]
- [nurse] Yes.

345
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:52,261
- [nurse] Because he's bigger.
- [Paldo] Right!

346
00:16:53,387 --> 00:16:54,638
[T-Bak] Oh, no.

347
00:16:55,431 --> 00:16:57,182
[sneaky music playing]

348
00:16:57,266 --> 00:16:58,392
Will this take long?

349
00:16:58,475 --> 00:16:59,685
I still have to go to the gym.

350
00:16:59,768 --> 00:17:01,520
[T-Bak panting]

351
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:03,981
[in English] O-M-… G.

352
00:17:04,064 --> 00:17:05,232
[T-Bak] Huh?

353
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:06,984
Oh, godchild!

354
00:17:07,067 --> 00:17:09,111
- Oh? How are you?
- Ah, Godfather. How are you?

355
00:17:09,194 --> 00:17:11,572
So? Can I sell here now?

356
00:17:11,655 --> 00:17:13,449
I really don't want to stay in our area.

357
00:17:13,532 --> 00:17:15,242
I want to avoid my ex.

358
00:17:15,325 --> 00:17:16,869
- [man] Oh!
- She's single?

359
00:17:17,453 --> 00:17:18,412
Ah, I'm single.

360
00:17:18,495 --> 00:17:19,997
[overlapping chatter]

361
00:17:20,664 --> 00:17:21,790
- Kap, oh!
- [Paldo] Hey.

362
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:23,333
[Kurt] She is my godchild.

363
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:26,211
This is the one I told you about,
the one who wants to sell here.

364
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:27,921
If that's okay.

365
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:29,840
Brother Kurt, of course.

366
00:17:30,424 --> 00:17:31,508
Ah, hi.

367
00:17:32,092 --> 00:17:35,095
I'm, uh… I'm Paldo Castro.

368
00:17:35,179 --> 00:17:36,096
Denden.

369
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:37,306
[nurse] Excuse me.

370
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:39,516
Can you talk outside first?

371
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,018
- [Kurt] Ah, sorry.
- [indistinct]

372
00:17:41,101 --> 00:17:41,935
- [nurse] Thank you.
- [Kurt] We'll talk outside then.

373
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:42,853
[Kurt] Let's go. Sorry.

374
00:17:44,813 --> 00:17:46,106
Return this blade.

375
00:17:47,107 --> 00:17:48,650
You took it.

376
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:50,360
Wow!

377
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:52,488
Why are there wigs here?

378
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:54,364
[suspicious music playing]

379
00:17:55,449 --> 00:17:58,160
And now you're touching them again!

380
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:00,746
Enough!

381
00:18:00,829 --> 00:18:02,331
Put this back!

382
00:18:03,332 --> 00:18:05,417
You're so boring to be with.

383
00:18:07,753 --> 00:18:11,465
What will you do… if I do this?

384
00:18:13,675 --> 00:18:16,804
[tense music playing]

385
00:18:16,887 --> 00:18:18,263
Don't do that.

386
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:24,520
[Janine] Uh…

387
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:26,355
What if I do this?

388
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:29,858
[Ibyang] Don't--

389
00:18:30,609 --> 00:18:31,568
See?

390
00:18:32,069 --> 00:18:33,862
You can't do anything.

391
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:35,447
Stay there.

392
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:36,657
Huh?

393
00:18:36,740 --> 00:18:39,451
- [Janine, in English] Bye.
- Help me fix this!

394
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:41,703
You made this mess!

395
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:47,793
[Paldo] Keep quiet, okay.

396
00:18:47,876 --> 00:18:50,796
[bustling chatter]

397
00:18:50,879 --> 00:18:52,965
[Denden] This is what I'll sell here.

398
00:18:53,048 --> 00:18:54,049
[Kurt] Ah! Okay.

399
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:57,469
Um, you know, Denden,

400
00:18:57,553 --> 00:19:00,472
I really support small businesses
here in our community.

401
00:19:01,348 --> 00:19:03,934
That's why I can support you.

402
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:07,229
[sneaky music playing]

403
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:08,772
So, what are you selling?

404
00:19:09,273 --> 00:19:10,691
What am I selling?

405
00:19:11,191 --> 00:19:13,610
- These! [chuckles]
- Ouch!

406
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:15,988
Here, this is really for you.

407
00:19:16,071 --> 00:19:17,156
- Really?
- [Denden] Yes.

408
00:19:17,239 --> 00:19:18,198
See, she said it's for me.

409
00:19:18,282 --> 00:19:19,032
[chuckles softly]

410
00:19:19,116 --> 00:19:21,285
[Paldo] Looks… Looks delicious.

411
00:19:21,368 --> 00:19:22,244
Is this delicious?

412
00:19:22,870 --> 00:19:23,704
It's sweet.

413
00:19:23,787 --> 00:19:24,746
[soft chuckle]

414
00:19:24,830 --> 00:19:25,706
- Bro, here.
- [man stammers]

415
00:19:25,789 --> 00:19:27,040
- Hold this first.
- [man] Ah, we'll take care of it.

416
00:19:27,124 --> 00:19:29,543
[lively chatter]

417
00:19:30,252 --> 00:19:32,045
- Hey!
- [man] Hey, relax.

418
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:33,172
[Paldo] Hey, that's mine!

419
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:34,381
[lively chatter]

420
00:19:34,464 --> 00:19:35,424
[Paldo] That's mine--

421
00:19:35,507 --> 00:19:37,467
Just a little, okay?

422
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:41,513
[tense music playing]

423
00:19:41,597 --> 00:19:42,431
[Denden] My phone!

424
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:43,473
- [Paldo] Huh?!
- [Kurt] Your phone?

425
00:19:43,557 --> 00:19:44,975
- [Paldo] Why?
- My phone got stolen!

426
00:19:45,058 --> 00:19:47,519
[clamoring]

427
00:19:51,064 --> 00:19:53,192
[screaming]

428
00:19:54,401 --> 00:19:56,278
[Emerson] Ouch!

429
00:19:56,945 --> 00:19:58,071
What was that?!

430
00:19:58,155 --> 00:20:00,407
Bro, really! Why weren't you looking?!

431
00:20:00,490 --> 00:20:02,826
This is a passageway, not a runway!

432
00:20:03,827 --> 00:20:06,455
- You just walked straight--
- [Denden] Thief! Thief!

433
00:20:06,538 --> 00:20:09,041
- [Denden] Thief! Thief!
- [Emerson] You thief?!

434
00:20:09,124 --> 00:20:10,042
[screaming] That's a thief!

435
00:20:10,125 --> 00:20:10,876
[grunts]

436
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:12,961
[grunts] So, you're a thief!

437
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:14,421
- [men grunt]
- [crowd screams]

438
00:20:15,172 --> 00:20:17,633
- [clamoring]
- [Emerson] Jerk! You thief! Hmm!

439
00:20:17,716 --> 00:20:19,218
- [grunting]
- [man] Beat him up!

440
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:21,303
[crowd] That's it, that's it!

441
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:23,263
[Emerson] You're a thief, ha?!

442
00:20:23,347 --> 00:20:24,640
- Huh?!
- [indistinct]

443
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:26,892
- [Emerson grunts]
- [Denden shrieks]

444
00:20:26,975 --> 00:20:28,060
[Emerson panting]

445
00:20:28,143 --> 00:20:30,896
[indistinct chattering]

446
00:20:30,979 --> 00:20:32,105
[grunts]

447
00:20:32,189 --> 00:20:34,024
Damn you! You thief!

448
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:37,110
Here. Miss, here's the--

449
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:39,529
[quirky sting]

450
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:41,281
What-- Miss?

451
00:20:41,365 --> 00:20:42,658
- [indistinct chattering]
- [Emerson] Miss, here's the--

452
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,035
- [Emerson] I don't know--
- [indistinct]

453
00:20:45,118 --> 00:20:45,953
Maybe she was hit--

454
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:48,038
- Miss, Miss, Miss?
- [indistinct]

455
00:20:48,121 --> 00:20:49,206
- Miss?
- [man] Denden.

456
00:20:49,289 --> 00:20:50,457
[woman] Beautiful!

457
00:20:55,128 --> 00:20:57,005
[Kurt] What hap-- What happened?!

458
00:20:57,089 --> 00:20:58,715
What did you do to my goddaughter?!

459
00:20:58,799 --> 00:21:00,133
- [Kurt] Huh?! Denden!
- [in English] So-- Sorry.

460
00:21:00,217 --> 00:21:02,970
Sorry. Maybe I hit her
when I was chasing the snatcher--

461
00:21:03,053 --> 00:21:05,222
[Kurt] So, it was you!
What did you do to my goddaughter?!

462
00:21:05,305 --> 00:21:07,057
Denden. Oh!

463
00:21:08,892 --> 00:21:09,977
[Atoy] Janine!

464
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:10,978
[soft chuckle]

465
00:21:11,061 --> 00:21:12,145
I'll make you Dinengdeng.

466
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:13,438
You want? It's delicious.

467
00:21:13,522 --> 00:21:15,065
Dinengdeng? What's that?

468
00:21:15,732 --> 00:21:17,818
- [Atoy] Dinengdeng.
- I don't like vegetables. That's yucky.

469
00:21:17,901 --> 00:21:18,735
[Atoy] You don't eat that?

470
00:21:19,569 --> 00:21:21,947
Okay, I'll make you something else.

471
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:24,825
Wait. What are you doing outside?
Why are you here?

472
00:21:24,908 --> 00:21:26,326
Ibyang sent me out.

473
00:21:26,827 --> 00:21:28,787
- Ibyang?
- [Janine sighs]

474
00:21:28,870 --> 00:21:30,831
Why? Did you fight again?

475
00:21:30,914 --> 00:21:32,833
I told her not to fight with you.
Where is she?

476
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:35,711
She's in that secret room,

477
00:21:35,794 --> 00:21:39,006
with the… clothes and knives?

478
00:21:39,089 --> 00:21:40,799
[tense music playing]

479
00:21:40,882 --> 00:21:41,800
What?

480
00:21:42,676 --> 00:21:44,219
Son of a thread.

481
00:21:51,101 --> 00:21:52,769
You're in trouble now.

482
00:21:52,853 --> 00:21:55,022
[chuckles softly]

483
00:22:04,072 --> 00:22:05,866
[pensive music playing]

484
00:22:05,949 --> 00:22:07,868
Didn't I tell you,

485
00:22:08,452 --> 00:22:10,329
you're not allowed to come in here?

486
00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:15,167
[tense music playing]

487
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:16,710
Why are you holding that?

488
00:22:18,086 --> 00:22:20,297
You shouldn't be touching this!

489
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:22,215
Didn't I tell you,
you're not allowed to come in here?

490
00:22:22,299 --> 00:22:23,842
What are you doing here?!

491
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:26,511
[pensive music playing]

492
00:22:27,304 --> 00:22:28,972
It was Janine who went in first.

493
00:22:29,056 --> 00:22:30,599
[sobs]

494
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:32,100
She opened this room--

495
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:34,728
Janine! You're blaming Janine again!

496
00:22:35,395 --> 00:22:36,855
Then why did you follow?

497
00:22:36,938 --> 00:22:39,941
[sobs] I was just stopping her.

498
00:22:40,025 --> 00:22:42,152
Stopping her? If you were stopping her,
why are you here?

499
00:22:42,235 --> 00:22:43,320
[heavy music playing]

500
00:22:43,403 --> 00:22:45,530
[gasps] Ibyang, really!

501
00:22:45,614 --> 00:22:46,990
What if something bad happened to you?

502
00:22:47,074 --> 00:22:48,658
What if you got hurt?!

503
00:22:49,659 --> 00:22:51,495
We already talked about this.

504
00:22:51,578 --> 00:22:53,789
It's off-limits, right?

505
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:57,334
If anyone should follow the rules,
it should be you.

506
00:22:57,417 --> 00:22:58,877
You should be the first!

507
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:02,380
You're unbelievable.

508
00:23:02,464 --> 00:23:04,216
I always tell you, Ibyang,

509
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:06,843
even when no one is watching,

510
00:23:06,927 --> 00:23:09,763
you must always do what is right.

511
00:23:10,347 --> 00:23:12,349
Didn't we have an understanding?

512
00:23:12,432 --> 00:23:14,684
[tense music playing]

513
00:23:14,768 --> 00:23:16,686
I was wrong to expect from you.

514
00:23:17,270 --> 00:23:19,356
Fine. Get out now!

515
00:23:21,650 --> 00:23:24,653
[dramatic music playing]

516
00:23:49,427 --> 00:23:51,721
I'm only doing my responsibility
as a father.

517
00:23:51,805 --> 00:23:52,764
Of your child?

518
00:23:52,848 --> 00:23:54,182
[Tonet] And what about Ibyang?

519
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:55,809
The child is pitiful.

520
00:23:55,892 --> 00:23:57,853
If you don't want her, then say it!

521
00:23:57,936 --> 00:24:00,689
Don't make her feel worthless!

522
00:24:00,772 --> 00:24:02,065
[Tonet] <i>Be fair, Atoy!</i>

523
00:24:02,691 --> 00:24:03,859
Where are we going?

524
00:24:03,942 --> 00:24:05,193
I'll take you both out.

525
00:24:05,277 --> 00:24:07,404
[Atoy] <i>Go to sleep.</i>
<i>I don't want fighting, okay?</i>

526
00:24:07,487 --> 00:24:09,614
Why did you even come back?
You're not his real child.

527
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:13,451
Isn't it unsettling that Atoy has been
with Janine for that long?

528
00:24:13,535 --> 00:24:16,580
What if he notices or finds out
that the child isn't his?

529
00:24:16,663 --> 00:24:18,081
- [Atoy] <i>Oh?</i>
- I'll take a picture of you.

530
00:24:18,165 --> 00:24:19,291
- [Atoy] <i>Oh, okay.</i>
- [photographer] You look so cute

531
00:24:19,374 --> 00:24:21,543
as father and child. You even look alike.

532
00:24:22,127 --> 00:24:23,545
Brother, hello?

533
00:24:23,628 --> 00:24:25,589
I'm the real child, not her.

534
00:24:25,672 --> 00:24:26,423
Well, wow.

535
00:24:26,506 --> 00:24:28,049
[nurse] What's the blood type again?

536
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:31,803
Both parents are O positive.

537
00:24:31,887 --> 00:24:34,931
But the child is AB positive.

538
00:24:35,015 --> 00:24:36,975
Oh, no. That's impossible.

539
00:24:37,058 --> 00:24:38,852
So, Janine isn't Atoy's child?

540
00:24:38,935 --> 00:24:40,395
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

541
00:24:40,478 --> 00:24:42,522
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

542
00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:46,359
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

543
00:24:46,443 --> 00:24:47,527
♪ <i>Fix it</i> ♪

544
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:48,653
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
